===Release history===
The game was initially hinted when Square Enix trademarked ''Hikari to Yami no Senshi'' which was initially believd to be related to [[Tactics Ogre: Let Us Cling Together]].<ref name="Trademark">{{cite web |author=Spencer |title= The Latest Square Enix Trademark Is Warrior Of Light And Darkness |url=http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |publisher=Siliconera |accessdate=2013-04-09 |date=2010-05-17}}</ref> It was announced in Japan as ''Final Fantasy Legends: Hikari to Yami no Senshi'' on July 21, 2010.<ref name="ASannounce">{{cite web |last=Gantayat |first=Anoop |title=Final Fantasy Legends Formally Announced |url=http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |publisher=[[Andriasang]] |accessdate=2011-03-08 |date=2010-07-21}}</ref> The first chapters of the game were first released for iMode phones on September 6, 2010, and for EZweb phones on December 9, 2010.<ref name="QJ">{{cite web |title= Final Fantasy Legends: Warriors of Light and Darkness detailed|url=http://www.qj.net/qjnet/news/final-fantasy-legends-warriors-of-light-and-darkness-detailed.html|publisher=[[QJ.NET]] |accessdate=2011-03-08}}</ref> The rest of the chapters were released approximately once a month since then till August 8, 2011 for iMode and November 10, 2011 for EZweb. On Tokyo Game Show of 2011, the game was announced to be released on iOS and Android with improved graphics and sound, and support for slide-pad controls over the feature phone version.<ref>{{cite web |title= Final Fantasy Legends Hits iOS and Android This Summer |url= http://andriasang.com/con1kv/ff_legends_smartphone/ |publisher=Andriasang |accessdate=2012-06-22}}</ref> On E3 2012, the iOS/Android version was announced internationally as ''Final Fantasy Dimensions'' also to be released on August 31, 2012.<ref name="DimensionsAnnounced">{{cite web |last=Schreier |first=Jason|title= Square Enix Is Releasing A Brand New, Original,Old-School Final Fantasy Game |url= http://kotaku.com/5916484/square-enix-is-releasing-a-brand-new-original-old%20school-final-fantasy-game |publisher=Kotaku |accessdate=2012-06-12 |date=2012-06-07}}</ref><ref name="DimensionsDate">{{cite web |last=Davis |first=Justin |title= Final Fantasy Dimensions Coming Later This Month |url= http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/08/23/final-fantasy-dimensions-coming-later-this-month |publisher=IGN |accessdate=2012-08-24 }}</ref> Due to technical difficulties, only "Prologue" was released first for the iOS version. All other chapters were purchasable at the in-app shop after upgrading from 1.0.0 to 1.0.1 which was available later in the same day.<ref name="RPGFan1">{{cite web |title= Final Fantasy Dimensions now Available |url= http://www.rpgfan.com/news/2012/1856.html |publisher=[[RPGFan]] |accessdate=2012-10-09}}</ref> The Android version was released on December 21, 2012 in its complete form.<ref>{{cite web |last=Patterson|first=Sean |title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Released for Android |url= http://www.webpronews.com/final-fantasy-dimensions-released-for-android-2012-12 |publisher=Web Pro News|accessdate=2013-03-06}}</ref> 

