== Reception ==
The game had received mainly positive reviews. Final Fantasy  Dimensions received an aggregated score of 78 on Metacritic based on 10 reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/final-fantasy-dimensions/critic-reviews |title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Critic Reviews for iPhone/iPad |publisher=Metacritic |date= |accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref> [[Slide to Play]] gave it a perfect score of 100 stating, "Square Enix has made a truly masterful game here. The story is huge, the characters enjoyable and fun to play, and other than the iffy controls, the game works fantastically well on the touchscreen. The menus in particular are elegantly designed. The music and graphics are even great in creating a world that reminds us that the old and new can coexist, and do so with aplomb".<ref>{{cite web|last=Carlson |first=Erik |url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/final-fantasy-dimensions-review/ |title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Review |publisher=Slide To Play |date=2012-09-05 |accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref> Justin Davis of [[IGN]] criticized the episodic structure of the game however "Players can't fully explore the game world until they're almost at the end <U+2013> over 30 hours in!", however also praises the gameplay stating, "What ''Dimensions'' lacks in scenario & story flexibility it makes up for with sheer depth and flexibility in its job system. Players can assign any party member to any available job on-the-fly, with more opening up as the story progresses."<ref name="IGNreview">{{cite web |last=Davis |first=Justin |title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Review |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/09/18/final-fantasy-dimensions-review |publisher=IGN |accessdate=2012-09-25 |date=2012-09-18}}</ref> [[Game Informer]] praised the gameplay but criticized the lack of fanfare stating, "Despite the fun job system and classic vibe to the combat, Dimensions seems like it was set up to fail. It released to little fanfare at a prohibitive price point for mobile games."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/final_fantasy_dimensions/b/ios/archive/2012/10/02/final-fantasy-dimensions-review.aspx |title=Fond Memories Can<U+2019>t Sustain This Mobile Adventure - Final Fantasy Dimensions - iOS |publisher=Game Informer|date=2012-10-02 |accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref> [[Toucharcade]] praised the games features stating, "There's an epic, high fantasy plot with lots of twists, a large cast of characters whose appearance and abilities vary wildly, tons of random combat, lots of leveling-up and abilities to unlock, a gradual opening up of the world, secret items, bonus dungeons, and a lot of looking inside pots and barrels in order to pilfer the worldly goods of the townspeople you run across."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2012/09/04/final-fantasy-dimensions-review-one-for-the-fans/ |title='Final Fantasy Dimensions' Review - One For the Fans (Review) |publisher=Touch Arcade |date=2012-09-04 |accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref> Derek Heemsbergen of RPGFan gave it a mixed review stating, "I'm grateful that the game was released in English, and while it isn't everything I hoped it would be, Final Fantasy: Dimensions does enough right to be worth playing."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rpgfan.com/reviews/Final_Fantasy_Dimensions/index.html |title=RPGFan Review - Final Fantasy: Dimensions |publisher=RPGFan |last=Heemsbergen |first=Derek |date=2012-09-24 |accessdate=2013-02-19}}</ref> Touchgen however, criticized the plot, the lack of animation, and sound of the game stating, "In the end, I cannot reconcile these cheapened portions of the game. I understand it is a port of a "mobile" game from Japan, but the quality of the port could have been much better. Had my three key issues with how the game presents itself not been present, I would probably have walked away feeling quite positive about Final Fantasy Dimensions. In its current form, though, I can only give it a middling score."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.touchgen.net/final-fantasy-dimensions|title= Final Fantasy: Dimensions |publisher=Touchgen |date=2012-09-15 |accessdate=2013-03-16}}</ref>

